<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880812-0170 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Allegheny Ludlum Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ALS WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> ALLEGHENY LUDLUM Corp. (Pittsburgh)  </DATELINE><TEXT>   This steelmaker named four new directors: James L. Murdy, Allegheny senior vice president, finance; Thomas Marshall, chairman and chief executive officer of Aristech Chemical Corp.; James E. Rohr, president of Pittsburgh National Bank; and Steven C. Wheelwright, a Harvard University management professor. Mr. Murdy fills a vacancy created by the death last February of Richard C. O'Sullivan; the other three fill new seats, increasing board membership to 12. </TEXT></DOC>